===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|肉|t1=meat|又|t2=hand|示|t3=altar, ceremony|ls=ic}} – the hand offers a piece of meat at the altar during a ceremony.

The {{och-l|*肉}} is turned on its side and appears as {{och-l|*𱼀}} in the regular script (compare {{zh-l|*將}}, {{zh-l|*然}}). The top right part is a form of {{lang|zh|又}}.

The top is not related to but may be corrupted to {{zh-l|*癶}} in calligraphy and handwriting; this form also appeared in the [[w:Second round of simplified Chinese characters|second-round simplified]] list.

